I want to create a comprehensive e-government system with the following features:

Basic Requirements:
- Frontend: React.js with Material UI
- Backend: Node.js + Express.js
- Database: MongoDB
- Authentication: JWT with roles (citizen, employee, administrator)

Required Features:
1. Integrated user interface supporting Arabic/English
2. Government services request system (12 core services)
3. Dashboard for each user type
4. Electronic appointment system
5. Electronic payment gateway
6. Instant notification system
7. Document upload/download
8. Live chat between citizen and employee
9. Integration with SMS system for sending notifications
- Dark mode support
- Advanced reports and statistics
- Service evaluation system

Technical Requirements:
- I want a complete, ready-to-execute code (not just examples)
- Full API documentation
- Step-by-step instructions on how to run the project
- Clear file structure for both Frontend and Backend
- Ensure all components work together seamlessly

Expected Output:
- Complete, ready-to-execute files
- Clear instructions on how to run the project
- Solutions to potential problems during implementation

Note: I want all code written in a clear and easy-to-understand language, with explanatory comments when necessary.
